-- Tunisia Allocates $2.9 Billion for Solar Energy Projects, News Agency Says
-- B y   J i h e n   L a g h m a r i
-- 2010-10-21T12:47:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/tunisia-allocates-2-9-billion-for-solar-energy-projects-news-agency-says.html
     Oct. 21 (Bloomberg) --The Tunisian government has allocated
$2.9 billion for investment in solar energy projects, the
official Tunisia News Agency said.  “This amount is allocated to fund 40 solar energy projects
to be achieved between 2010-2016,” the agency cited Abdul Aziz
Rassaa, secretary of state for energy at the ministry of
industry, as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jihen Laghmari in Cairo at 
 jlaghmari@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Digby Lidstone at 
 dlidstone@bloomberg.net  